<t>
<field>XX.LOCAL.REF</field>
<desc>
            <p>Standard T24 local reference field.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>User defined.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>SEC.ACCOUNT</field>
<desc>
            <p>The list of SEC.ACC.MASTER keys that will be grouped together for CGT purposes.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>Must belong to the same CUSTOMER as the key.</p>
            <p>Cannot be moved between groups if positions exist in any         securities.</p>
            <p>Cannot be deleted from a group if positions exist in any         securities.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>CUSTOMER.CODE</field>
<desc>
            <p>The customer under which CGT processing is required.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>Must be in CUSTOMER.SECURITY</p>
            <p>Must be CUSTOMER type in CUSTOMER.SECURITY</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>GROUP.NAME</field>
<desc>
            <p>The name under which portfolios will be grouped for CGT purposes. As many groups as required may be created but if a group &amp;#145;ALL&amp;#146; is entered it must be the only group.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>Can         only contain the following characters, A to Z, 0 to 9,         ()+-</p>
            <p>If         group ALL is used it must be the only group. </p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>LOCAL.REF</field>
<desc>
            <p>Standard T24 local reference field.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>Defined by the User</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>OVERRIDE</field>
<desc>
            <p>Standard T24 Override field.</p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>NOINPUT</p>
        </desc>
</t>
